---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AI Strategy Advisory"
  description="AI Strategy Advisory for enterprise leaders. Build AI strategies connected to operating models, governance frameworks and measurable business outcomes."
>

  <section class="section-py bg-[#05070D]" aria-labelledby="ai-strategy-heading">
    <div class="container-site">

      <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/advisory" class="text-white/40 text-sm hover:text-white/65 transition-colors">
          ← Advisory
        </a>
      </nav>

      <span class="eyebrow">Advisory · AI Strategy</span>

      <h1 id="ai-strategy-heading" class="text-section font-heading font-bold text-white mt-2 mb-6 max-w-[20ch]">
        AI Strategy Advisory
      </h1>

      <p class="text-white/65 text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-[56ch] mb-6">
        Most AI strategies fail not because of poor technology choices, but because
        the operating model was never redesigned to execute them. As an AI Strategy Advisor,
        I help enterprise organizations build AI strategies that connect investment decisions
        to operating model realities and governance structures.
      </p>

      <p class="text-white/50 leading-relaxed max-w-[56ch] mb-12">
        The advisory covers AI roadmap design, AI governance frameworks, AI program
        prioritization, and the organizational capabilities needed to move from AI pilots
        to embedded, scalable AI practices. Particular depth in banking and financial
        services transformation contexts.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">
          Book Advisory Call
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/advisory" class="btn-outline">All Advisory Services</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
